Spain, Germany and the Netherlands
won to maintain their perfect starts in qualifying for soccerâ€™s
2012 European Championship.  Fernando Llorente scored two goals to lead Spain over
Lithuania 3-1. The world and European champion has six points
from two games to lead Group I.  Miroslav Klose scored twice as Germany beat Turkey 3-0 in
Berlin in Group A and the Netherlands won 1-0  1-0 in Moldova in
Group E, giving each its third straight win.  Montenegro and Norway also won for the third straight time.
Montenegro defeated Switzerland 1-0 in Group G and Norway won 2-
1 at Cyprus.  Italy tied 0-0 in Northern Ireland to stay atop Group C by
one point over Estonia, a 3-1 winner in Serbia. Russia won 3-2
in Ireland, leaving the two tied in Group B with Slovakia, which
lost 3-1 in Armenia.  Georgia and Greece share the lead in Group F after both won
1-0, while Albania and Belarus lead group D after each played a
draw.  The next round of qualifying games will be played Oct. 12.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
